data.title: DEATH OF SAINT LOUIS, Louis IX, King of France -1901 Historical Print
data.meta_description: Louis IX, commonly known as Saint Louis or Louis the Saint, was King of France from 1226 to 1270, and the most illustrious of the Direct Capetians. He was crowned in Reims at the age of 12, following the death of his father Louis VIII.
